HEADWORD: Amateurish
<hw>Am`a*teur"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>In the style of an amateur;
superficial or defective like the work of an amateur.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Am`a*teur"ish*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Am`a*teur"ish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

